The "workhorse for big jobs." Low resolution but can print structures up to ~10 mm³.

### [25x_objective/overview.md](25x_objective/overview.md)
The sweet spot for most research. Balanced resolution (~1 µm features) and reasonable speed. Paired with IP-S resist.

### [63x_objective/overview.md](63x_objective/overview.md)
When you need the best. Sub-200 nm features. The lens physically dips into the liquid resist (DiLL mode) for refractive index matching.

