## Quick Decision Guide

```
What size is your structure?

  ├── < 100 µm (sub-micron features needed)
  │     └──► Use 63× + IP-Dip2
  │
  ├── 100 µm – 1 mm (moderate detail)
  │     └──► Use 25× + IP-S (or IP-Visio for bio)
  │
  ├── 1 mm – 10 mm+ (large, fast)
  │     └──► Use 10× + IP-Q
  │
  └── 2D pattern on wafer only
        └──► Use 20× + i-line resist (spin-coated)
```

---

## Before You Install ANY Objective

1. Make sure the **green "Process" light is OFF** before opening the top hatch
2. Press **"Exchange Holder"** button in NanoWrite first — this moves the piezo to safe position
3. Press **"Open"** — the button will flash; only then open the lid
4. Handle objectives **by their body**, never by the front element
5. Insert **only until rotation stops** — do NOT overtighten

